---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '@/components/PortfolioHeader.astro';
import Footer from '@/components/Footer.astro';
import Terminal from '@/components/Terminal.astro';
import { site } from '@/data/site';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy"
  description="Privacy and aggregate analytics policy for Mohit Sharma's portfolio."
>
  <Nav />
  <main id="main" class="section">
    <article class="container policy">
      <a class="back mono" href="/">← Portfolio</a>
      <p class="section-label">Privacy · Analytics</p>
      <h1>Measure the work, not the visitor.</h1>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          This is a static portfolio. It has no account system, advertising network,
          session replay, fingerprinting, or contact form database.
        </p>
        <h2>Aggregate analytics</h2>
        <p>
          When configured, this site sends bounded events to a collector owned by the
          site operator and hosted on Cloudflare Workers with aggregate storage in
          Cloudflare D1. There is no third-party analytics product or public dashboard.
          If the collector endpoint is not configured, no analytics request is made.
        </p>
        <p>The site limits command measurement to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>contact and résumé actions;</li>
          <li>project live-site and source-code actions;</li>
          <li>work-detail and blog opens.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>When the optional engagement layer is enabled, it also counts:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>foreground section milestones at 3, 10, and 30 seconds;</li>
          <li>manual project or case selection and explicitly opened feature hotspots;</li>
          <li>article progress at 25%, 50%, and 90%, plus evidence-ledger opening;</li>
          <li>allowlisted broad landing sources such as LinkedIn, GitHub, a job board, or a role-level résumé variant.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Foreground milestones accrue only while the section intersects the middle of
          the viewport, the page is visible and focused, and the browser has not been
          idle for 60 seconds. They are coarse gates, not exact reading time. Autoplay,
          hover previews, and scripted carousel motion are not counted as interest.
          Landing-source attribution ends on that page and is never propagated into a
          cross-page journey. Unknown, company-specific, vacancy-specific, recipient,
          and application identifiers are not accepted.
        </p>
        <p>
          Event properties are limited to the current route, a stable content ID, and
          the command's placement. The collector may add coarse country and device class
          and stores only a referrer's hostname. Query strings, URL fragments, IP
          addresses, full user agents, email addresses, free-form text, résumé contents,
          persistent identifiers, and individual visitor records are not stored.
          Engagement, article-progress, and landing-source rows deliberately discard
          country, device, and referrer context before storage. Aggregate rows are deleted
          after 24 months.
        </p>
        <h2>Optional context choice</h2>
        <p>
          Baseline aggregate analytics remains cookieless. You may separately allow
          coarse visit context. The choice sets one first-party preference cookie named
          <code>pa_context_consent</code> whose value is only <code>granted</code> or
          <code>denied</code>. It expires after 180 days, contains no random identifier,
          and is not sent to the analytics Worker.
        </p>
        <p>
          After opt-in, each consented pageview lets Cloudflare add three independent
          counters: country, country-region code, and ASN/network organization. These
          dimensions are stored in separate rows without route or engagement data, cannot
          be joined to one another, and are deleted after 90 days. City, precise location,
          IP address, and a visitor identifier are not stored. A network organization may
          be an ISP, VPN, university, cloud provider, or corporate network; it does not
          establish a visitor's employer.
        </p>
        <p>
          “Allow optional context” and “Continue without enrichment” are equally available.
          You can reopen “Analytics choices” on any page to change or withdraw the choice.
          Declining does not alter the site and does not stop the existing cookieless
          aggregate counters described above.
        </p>
        <p>
          The dashboard cannot identify unique visitors, reconstruct sessions or
          cross-page funnels, report exact time on a section, or reveal who viewed an
          item. Percentages are shown only after their denominator reaches 20; smaller
          samples remain counts rather than implied conclusions.
        </p>
        <h2>Privacy signals</h2>
        <p>
          If your browser sends Global Privacy Control or Do Not Track, this site skips
          analytics initialization, and the collector independently treats those request
          headers as a successful no-op. Those signals also suppress the optional context
          prompt and override a previously granted preference. Analytics is also disabled during local development
          and remains non-essential: blocking or losing the collector cannot change any
          page, command, download, or contact path.
        </p>
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about this policy can be sent to
          <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer />
  <Terminal />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  main { background: var(--cp-bg-elevated); }
  .policy { max-width: 900px; }
  .back { display: inline-block; margin-bottom: 48px; color: var(--cp-accent); font-size: var(--type-label); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; }
  h1 { max-width: 14ch; margin-bottom: 56px; font-size: var(--type-feature); }
  .prose { margin-inline: auto; }
  @media (max-width: 620px) { h1 { font-size: 3.25rem; } }
</style>